= Quick Reference Link: =

http://www.h2database.com/html/grammar.html

= Some Example Queries: =

=== LEFT ===
Below query displays whatever is before '@' in EMAIL column of table PUBLIC.MOCKDATA
<source>SELECT LEFT(EMAIL, INSTR(EMAIL,'@') - 1) FROM PUBLIC.MOCKDATA;</source>

Eg. if '''EMAIL''' is '''example@fluidops.com''' then the result will be '''example'''

=== CONCAT_WS ===
Below query concatenates FIRST_NAME and LAST_NAME and displays them under FULL_NAME column 
<source>SELECT CONCAT_WS(' ',FIRST_NAME,LAST_NAME) AS FULL_NAME FROM PUBLIC.MOCKDATA;</source>

Eg. if '''FIRST_NAME''' is '''Fluid''' and '''LAST_NAME''' is '''Operations''' then the result will be '''Fluid Operations'''

=== Trim ===
Below query removes whitespaces at the end of each email and displays whatever is left in EMAIL column of table PUBLIC.MOCKDATA
<source>SELECT TRIM(email) from PUBLIC.MOCKDATA;
</source>

Eg. if '''Email''' is '''example@fluid ops.com ''' then the result will be '''example@fluidops.com'''

=== REGEXP_REPLACE ===
Below query replaces '@' in any email with a whitespace
<source>SELECT REGEXP_REPLACE(EMAIL, '@', ' ') from PUBLIC.MOCKDATA;</source>

Eg. if '''EMAIL''' is '''example@fluidops.com''' then the result will be '''example fluidops.com'''